    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk the <strong>creamy stock</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5-6 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once you have a thick sauce, stir through your<strong> Dijon mustard </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheddar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) then season with a good grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
